ANALYSIS COMPLETE
====================================================================================================

Key Insights:
  1. DiT backbone dominates latency (runs N denoising steps)
  2. Image/Text encoders are relatively fast (run once)
  3. DiT caching (16→4 steps) provides ~4x speedup
  4. Flash variant (1 step) provides ~16x speedup vs standard

Note: These are theoretical estimates. Actual performance includes:
  - CUDA kernel optimizations (torch.compile, CUDA graphs)
  - Post-training quantization (FP8/NVFP4 on GB200)
  - CFG parallelism (2 GPUs for conditional/unconditional)
  - VAE encoding/decoding overhead (not modeled here)
